1
00:00:14,800 --> 00:00:17,680
Why am I so nervous all of a sudden?

2
00:00:17,680 --> 00:00:19,680
What's there to be nervous about?

3
00:00:19,680 --> 00:00:21,540
Just nervous. Of course I am.

4
00:00:26,080 --> 00:00:27,510
My head's a bit messy.

5
00:00:31,320 --> 00:00:32,840
I need to calm down.

6
00:00:32,840 --> 00:00:33,760
It's okay.

7
00:00:33,760 --> 00:00:34,900
Just relax.

8
00:00:41,360 --> 00:00:43,160
Actually, I didn't prepare a long speech.

9
00:00:43,160 --> 00:00:44,220
Because I want to...

10
00:00:45,360 --> 00:00:46,760
Since we've talked a lot,

11
00:00:46,760 --> 00:00:49,920
I thought I'd keep it brief this time.

12
00:00:51,360 --> 00:00:53,500
I got you a little gift.

13
00:00:57,640 --> 00:00:58,840
It's Kuromi.

14
00:00:58,840 --> 00:00:59,590
Yeah.

15
00:01:00,840 --> 00:01:01,380
Let me see.

16
00:01:02,040 --> 00:01:04,490
Because you said Kuromi is your favorite.

17
00:01:05,240 --> 00:01:06,810
And I happened to find one.

18
00:01:07,440 --> 00:01:09,120
When you go back to Singapore,

19
00:01:09,120 --> 00:01:10,480
I hope you'll be...

20
00:01:11,520 --> 00:01:12,970
just like Kuromi.

21
00:01:14,040 --> 00:01:15,120
Take good care of yourself,

22
00:01:15,120 --> 00:01:18,320
and call me often to stay in touch.

23
00:01:18,320 --> 00:01:19,910
Don't forget me, okay?

24
00:01:19,910 --> 00:01:20,200
Okay.

25
00:01:21,120 --> 00:01:22,300
I'll be waiting for your call.

26
00:01:25,920 --> 00:01:27,280
Can't you call me?

27
00:01:27,280 --> 00:01:29,090
Sure. We'll keep calling each other.

28
00:01:29,960 --> 00:01:30,840
Alright, call me.

29
00:01:30,840 --> 00:01:32,300
Call me.

30
00:01:35,240 --> 00:01:38,240
I also got you a...

31
00:01:40,440 --> 00:01:41,440
A photo album.

32
00:01:41,550 --> 00:01:43,110
It's full of us.

33
00:01:44,560 --> 00:01:45,520
This is our...

34
00:01:45,520 --> 00:01:47,200
This is our very first photo.

35
00:01:48,490 --> 00:01:48,890
Right?

36
00:01:49,560 --> 00:01:50,720
And there's more,

37
00:01:50,720 --> 00:01:51,800
like the ones

38
00:01:51,800 --> 00:01:54,280
we took at the lighthouse.

39
00:01:54,280 --> 00:01:56,120
I think they're beautiful.

40
00:02:00,240 --> 00:02:01,280
Making this album,

41
00:02:01,280 --> 00:02:03,910
brought back so many memories.

42
00:02:08,440 --> 00:02:10,670
It's my first time making something like this.

43
00:02:11,640 --> 00:02:12,840
While I was working on it,

44
00:02:12,840 --> 00:02:16,280
laying out the photos one by one-

45
00:02:16,280 --> 00:02:19,160
it felt like reliving a movie,

46
00:02:19,160 --> 00:02:20,640
every little moment.

47
00:02:21,640 --> 00:02:23,160
So under each photo,

48
00:02:23,160 --> 00:02:25,100
I wrote a little message for her.

49
00:02:25,100 --> 00:02:26,280
(Our first photo)

50
00:02:26,280 --> 00:02:29,360
Three, two, one.

51
00:02:29,360 --> 00:02:30,560
Look at me.

52
00:02:30,560 --> 00:02:31,480
Thanks.

53
00:02:31,480 --> 00:02:33,520
This Polaroid came out pink!

54
00:02:33,520 --> 00:02:34,640
Different colors.

55
00:02:34,640 --> 00:02:35,960
(Our first photo)
Black-pink.

56
00:02:35,960 --> 00:02:37,040
(In perfect sync)
Don't be nervous.

57
00:02:37,040 --> 00:02:38,880
You two should lean in closer.

58
00:02:38,880 --> 00:02:40,120
Closer?

59
00:02:40,120 --> 00:02:40,440
Enda,

60
00:02:40,440 --> 00:02:41,440
put your arm around her.

61
00:02:42,160 --> 00:02:43,350
So pretty.

62
00:02:43,350 --> 00:02:45,700
(Two professionals)

63
00:02:45,880 --> 00:02:46,480
You're the

64
00:02:46,480 --> 00:02:49,020
(Theme: First Meeting)
first girl I had feelings for.

65
00:02:49,240 --> 00:02:50,240
(A perfect match!)
I want to kiss you.

66
00:02:50,240 --> 00:02:51,390
Help me.

67
00:02:51,410 --> 00:02:52,520
(My favorite. Yang's a pro.)
So sharp.

68
00:02:52,520 --> 00:02:54,360
You look just like Jay Chou.

69
00:02:54,360 --> 00:02:56,250
(Your smile is so sweet!)
Stunning!

70
00:02:56,720 --> 00:02:58,000
(We're holding hands!)
I'm so happy.

71
00:02:58,840 --> 00:03:00,960
(So my answer is "I love you.")
Enda, Yang.

72
00:03:00,960 --> 00:03:02,240
You can take this promise back.

73
00:03:02,240 --> 00:03:04,130
Otherwise, it feels like signing a contract.

74
00:03:04,130 --> 00:03:05,660
(Contract
I'll always love Zhao Enda. Signed by:)

75
00:03:08,440 --> 00:03:11,230
There are so many more photos.

76
00:03:12,360 --> 00:03:14,120
We took tons that day.

77
00:03:14,120 --> 00:03:15,520
They're all amazing.

78
00:03:16,840 --> 00:03:18,040
This is so thoughtful.

79
00:03:22,160 --> 00:03:23,660
I'm really happy

80
00:03:24,520 --> 00:03:26,080
to have had this experience,

81
00:03:26,080 --> 00:03:28,010
to be a part of your life, and for us to

82
00:03:29,040 --> 00:03:30,200
mean something to each other.

83
00:03:32,640 --> 00:03:36,520
Everyone says you're a smart young woman

84
00:03:36,520 --> 00:03:38,120
with a strong presence,

85
00:03:38,120 --> 00:03:40,640
but I've never seen you that way.

86
00:03:40,640 --> 00:03:41,120
To me,

87
00:03:41,120 --> 00:03:43,290
you've always been a little girl.

88
00:03:43,290 --> 00:03:45,220
(You'll be my little girl forever.)

89
00:03:46,480 --> 00:03:48,840
And you've asked me

90
00:03:48,840 --> 00:03:50,640
what kind of person I like.

91
00:03:50,640 --> 00:03:53,390
Honestly, I never had a clear answer.

92
00:03:58,760 --> 00:03:59,870
Until I met you.

93
00:04:01,760 --> 00:04:04,040
I realized everything felt just right.

94
00:04:04,100 --> 00:04:06,860
(Until I met you, everything felt just right.)

95
00:04:06,880 --> 00:04:07,840
Is this porridge?

96
00:04:07,840 --> 00:04:09,960
Yes, but it might've been out too long.

97
00:04:09,960 --> 00:04:11,040
It's thick.

98
00:04:11,040 --> 00:04:12,440
It's fine.

99
00:04:12,440 --> 00:04:13,880
Just add some hot water.

100
00:04:13,880 --> 00:04:14,640
I know you're cold,

101
00:04:14,640 --> 00:04:15,780
but I only found this.

102
00:04:20,840 --> 00:04:23,280
Thanks.

103
00:04:23,280 --> 00:04:24,510
Adjust the flowers a bit.

104
00:04:25,480 --> 00:04:26,760
You're beautiful.

105
00:04:26,760 --> 00:04:28,560
I peeled three shrimp for you.

106
00:04:28,560 --> 00:04:29,520
That's so sweet.

107
00:04:29,520 --> 00:04:30,640
It's freezing.

108
00:04:30,640 --> 00:04:31,460
Let me warm your hands.

109
00:04:41,830 --> 00:04:42,760
Yang.

110
00:04:44,440 --> 00:04:45,140
I like you.

111
00:04:57,280 --> 00:05:00,320
Every day with you makes me happy.

112
00:05:00,320 --> 00:05:01,640
Whatever we do makes me happy.

113
00:05:01,640 --> 00:05:03,310
Even doing nothing makes me happy.

114
00:05:08,880 --> 00:05:12,080
But as this joy comes to an end,

115
00:05:12,080 --> 00:05:12,980
I feel a little sad.

116
00:05:16,480 --> 00:05:18,200
Because the distance between us

117
00:05:18,200 --> 00:05:19,740
isn't quite right.

118
00:05:31,960 --> 00:05:33,760
You live in Singapore now?

119
00:05:33,760 --> 00:05:34,480
Yeah.

120
00:05:34,480 --> 00:05:36,640
And you only come back
to China once in a while?

121
00:05:36,640 --> 00:05:37,120
Yes.

122
00:05:37,120 --> 00:05:38,240
Why?

123
00:05:38,240 --> 00:05:39,400
Why do you ask?

124
00:05:39,400 --> 00:05:41,200
Nothing, just curious.

125
00:05:41,200 --> 00:05:43,400
I've never believed in
long-distance relationships.

126
00:05:43,400 --> 00:05:44,680
So ever since then,

127
00:05:44,680 --> 00:05:46,320
I've become very rational.

128
00:05:46,320 --> 00:05:48,200
I'm done with long-distance relationships.

129
00:05:48,200 --> 00:05:49,120
I've dated someone

130
00:05:49,120 --> 00:05:49,680
younger before,

131
00:05:49,680 --> 00:05:50,760
and I'm done with that too.

132
00:05:50,760 --> 00:05:52,160
And now, it's happening again.

133
00:05:52,160 --> 00:05:53,360
Yang,

134
00:05:53,360 --> 00:05:54,840
maybe these words-

135
00:05:54,840 --> 00:05:55,720
Feel too heavy.

136
00:05:55,720 --> 00:05:57,120
Yeah, way too heavy.

137
00:05:57,120 --> 00:05:58,000
I'm really worried

138
00:05:58,000 --> 00:05:59,960
that once you're back to your normal life

139
00:05:59,960 --> 00:06:00,560
and work,

140
00:06:00,560 --> 00:06:02,080
you'll realize

141
00:06:02,080 --> 00:06:02,880
you're just fine

142
00:06:02,880 --> 00:06:04,140
without Zhao Enda.

143
00:06:04,880 --> 00:06:06,000
But what if I get tired?

144
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:06,720
You haven't tried.

145
00:06:06,720 --> 00:06:07,520
How can you be tired?

146
00:06:07,520 --> 00:06:08,280
I have. I've done

147
00:06:08,280 --> 00:06:09,160
long-distance before.

148
00:06:09,160 --> 00:06:09,720
So did you.

149
00:06:09,720 --> 00:06:10,760
I did, but I forgot.

150
00:06:10,760 --> 00:06:11,760
I remember.

151
00:06:11,760 --> 00:06:13,580
I think we should break up.

152
00:06:16,880 --> 00:06:17,730
Yang!

153
00:06:30,800 --> 00:06:31,600
Yesterday,

154
00:06:32,840 --> 00:06:34,310
I finally found my answer.

155
00:06:44,400 --> 00:06:48,340
I don't see distance as an obstacle to

156
00:06:49,840 --> 00:06:50,870
our relationship,

157
00:06:51,800 --> 00:06:54,040
but as a unique prologue

158
00:06:54,040 --> 00:06:54,830
to our story.

159
00:06:55,140 --> 00:06:58,260
(Long-distance,
a unique prologue to our story.)

160
00:06:58,680 --> 00:07:01,640
They say love mirrors the pain,

161
00:07:01,640 --> 00:07:03,200
(Love mirrors the pain.)
but I believe

162
00:07:03,200 --> 00:07:05,400
(Love conquers all.)
love conquers all.

163
00:07:05,400 --> 00:07:06,690
So, Yang…

164
00:07:10,080 --> 00:07:11,470
Would you be with me?

165
00:07:11,980 --> 00:07:18,260
(Would you be with me?)

166
00:07:18,280 --> 00:07:19,370
I would.

167
00:07:19,370 --> 00:07:20,920
(I would.)

168
00:07:20,920 --> 00:07:21,570
Yes!

169
00:07:41,680 --> 00:07:42,880
I promise you I'll go

170
00:07:42,880 --> 00:07:44,120
to Singapore to see you.

171
00:07:44,120 --> 00:07:45,490
If once isn't enough, then twice.

172
00:07:46,200 --> 00:07:47,480
If twice isn't enough, then three times.

173
00:07:47,480 --> 00:07:48,680
Let's give it a shot.

174
00:07:48,680 --> 00:07:50,680
I'll go to Singapore to see you.

175
00:07:50,680 --> 00:07:52,000
I'll stay there for a while.

176
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:53,320
You still want to give it a shot?

177
00:07:53,320 --> 00:07:53,860
Yes.

178
00:07:54,800 --> 00:07:55,920
Failed again.

179
00:07:56,680 --> 00:07:57,690
I need to try again.

180
00:07:59,000 --> 00:07:59,720
When I play games,

181
00:07:59,720 --> 00:08:00,800
I don't keep losing.

182
00:08:00,800 --> 00:08:01,680
I've got to win.

183
00:08:01,680 --> 00:08:02,680
I always play to win.

184
00:08:02,680 --> 00:08:04,600
I can't just fail a level

185
00:08:04,600 --> 00:08:06,120
and then give up on it forever.

186
00:08:06,120 --> 00:08:09,400
Let's take it step by step,

187
00:08:09,400 --> 00:08:12,280
see where each step takes us,

188
00:08:12,280 --> 00:08:15,120
and overcome whatever comes our way.

189
00:08:34,470 --> 00:08:38,240
Kiss!

190
00:08:41,220 --> 00:08:45,360
Kiss!

191
00:08:49,800 --> 00:08:50,480
I can't see.

192
00:08:50,480 --> 00:08:51,400
Enda, kiss her!

193
00:08:51,400 --> 00:08:52,240
Kiss her!

194
00:09:01,240 --> 00:09:03,080
Yang!

195
00:09:03,080 --> 00:09:04,720
I love this!

196
00:09:06,090 --> 00:09:07,440
Thanks, everyone.

197
00:09:07,440 --> 00:09:08,820
Thanks, you guys.

198
00:09:09,600 --> 00:09:12,690
Congratulations!

199
00:09:14,240 --> 00:09:14,700
Let's go.

200
00:09:20,400 --> 00:09:22,120
At last, I spoke all that

201
00:09:22,120 --> 00:09:23,880
I most wanted to say.

202
00:09:23,880 --> 00:09:26,200
It made everything I've done worth it.

203
00:09:26,200 --> 00:09:27,880
I feel so happy.

204
00:09:27,880 --> 00:09:28,760
There are many blank pages

205
00:09:28,760 --> 00:09:30,240
at the back of this album.

206
00:09:30,240 --> 00:09:34,000
I hope after we leave Balance Island,

207
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:35,480
we can fill them up together.

208
00:09:35,480 --> 00:09:36,880
I'm so happy,

209
00:09:36,880 --> 00:09:38,600
overjoyed and deeply moved.

210
00:09:38,600 --> 00:09:40,920
In the end, he could firmly say that

211
00:09:40,920 --> 00:09:43,080
after both rational
and emotional consideration,

212
00:09:43,080 --> 00:09:44,690
he still chose me.

213
00:09:45,840 --> 00:09:46,860
Congratulations to you.

214
00:09:47,760 --> 00:09:48,880
You did it.

215
00:09:48,880 --> 00:09:49,800
Congratulations.

216
00:09:49,800 --> 00:09:50,680
Wishing you happiness.

217
00:09:50,680 --> 00:09:51,520
How about you?

218
00:09:52,440 --> 00:09:54,800
That was awesome!

219
00:09:55,440 --> 00:09:57,000
Congrats! I'm so happy for you.

220
00:09:57,000 --> 00:09:58,040
You look gorgeous.

221
00:09:58,040 --> 00:09:59,120
You too.

222
00:09:59,120 --> 00:09:59,880
Thank you.

223
00:09:59,880 --> 00:10:02,240
Thanks. Your shoes gave me strength.

224
00:10:02,240 --> 00:10:03,040
Really?

225
00:10:03,040 --> 00:10:04,840
The strength was already in you.

226
00:10:04,840 --> 00:10:05,480
It came from you.

227
00:10:05,480 --> 00:10:06,040
Be happy forever.

228
00:10:06,040 --> 00:10:07,040
For real?

229
00:10:07,040 --> 00:10:07,640
Yang.

230
00:10:09,480 --> 00:10:10,080
Thanks, Pascal.

231
00:10:10,080 --> 00:10:10,880
Be happy forever.

232
00:10:10,880 --> 00:10:11,400
So happy.

233
00:10:11,400 --> 00:10:12,440
Thanks, village chief.

234
00:10:12,440 --> 00:10:13,400
Where did he kiss you?

235
00:10:13,400 --> 00:10:14,200
On the cheek.

236
00:10:14,200 --> 00:10:15,400
Which side?

237
00:10:15,400 --> 00:10:16,080
This side.

238
00:10:16,080 --> 00:10:17,200
Don't wash your face tonight.

239
00:10:18,110 --> 00:10:18,760
On her cheek.

240
00:10:19,280 --> 00:10:20,480
Han, how did it go for you guys?

241
00:10:20,480 --> 00:10:20,840
It's over.

242
00:10:20,840 --> 00:10:21,880
Why?

243
00:10:21,880 --> 00:10:22,970
We're not right for each other.

244
00:10:23,800 --> 00:10:24,800
Why?

245
00:10:24,800 --> 00:10:25,800
I think they are.

246
00:10:26,400 --> 00:10:27,520
What's not right?

247
00:10:27,520 --> 00:10:28,320
Is it the hair?

248
00:10:28,320 --> 00:10:29,950
If it is, just blow-dry it again.

249
00:10:30,890 --> 00:10:31,680
What did you say?

250
00:10:31,680 --> 00:10:32,720
Nothing, I just...

251
00:10:32,720 --> 00:10:33,720
Are you messing with me?

252
00:10:33,720 --> 00:10:34,600
- Another prank?
- No.

253
00:10:34,600 --> 00:10:36,380
I don't think I like her enough yet.

254
00:10:36,960 --> 00:10:38,800
That guy deserves an Oscar.

255
00:10:38,800 --> 00:10:40,020
What a veteran actor.

256
00:10:41,240 --> 00:10:42,600
Absolutely!

257
00:10:43,200 --> 00:10:44,320
We're friends now.

258
00:10:44,320 --> 00:10:45,400
Still messing with me, huh?

259
00:10:45,400 --> 00:10:46,440
Is that true?

260
00:10:46,440 --> 00:10:47,480
He's a veteran actor.

261
00:10:47,480 --> 00:10:48,800
No way.

262
00:10:48,800 --> 00:10:49,570
I don't buy it.

263
00:10:51,040 --> 00:10:51,860
He's messing with me.

264
00:10:52,280 --> 00:10:53,520
Why did you buy flowers?

265
00:10:53,520 --> 00:10:55,320
We agreed to keep it simple.

266
00:10:55,320 --> 00:10:57,680
I can't take them with me.

267
00:10:57,680 --> 00:10:58,640
It's okay.

268
00:10:58,640 --> 00:11:00,580
Love always starts with a bouquet.

269
00:11:01,400 --> 00:11:02,280
How did I hug you?

270
00:11:02,280 --> 00:11:03,500
Was it like this?

271
00:11:05,480 --> 00:11:06,790
Oh, it should be like this.

272
00:11:09,880 --> 00:11:10,800
I really like you.

273
00:11:13,080 --> 00:11:14,200
I was freaking out.

274
00:11:14,200 --> 00:11:15,560
Really?

275
00:11:15,560 --> 00:11:16,560
That was amazing.

276
00:11:16,560 --> 00:11:17,880
You did it great.

277
00:11:17,880 --> 00:11:19,080
I'm truly touched.

278
00:11:19,080 --> 00:11:19,960
You're incredible.

279
00:11:19,960 --> 00:11:21,430
You look so handsome with your bangs up.

280
00:11:22,480 --> 00:11:23,080
So handsome.

281
00:11:23,080 --> 00:11:23,560
Really?

282
00:11:23,560 --> 00:11:24,130
Very handsome.

283
00:11:24,680 --> 00:11:26,550
You looked handsome holding the bouquet.

284
00:11:35,680 --> 00:11:36,920
Do you really mean it?

285
00:11:37,880 --> 00:11:38,930
Of course I do.

286
00:11:40,760 --> 00:11:42,610
Come on, let's check out the next one.

287
00:11:46,360 --> 00:11:47,790
You can kiss me all you want tonight.

288
00:11:54,240 --> 00:11:55,550
Honestly, I'm kinda jealous.

289
00:11:56,980 --> 00:11:59,020
(Same here, man.)

290
00:11:59,040 --> 00:11:59,920
Really jealous.

291
00:11:59,920 --> 00:12:00,540
Totally.

292
00:12:01,320 --> 00:12:02,080
I was thinking,

